narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would definitely recommend the course. The course is a fair deal of work, but worth the incredible trove of knowledge you garner. I would recommend that undergrads talk to the professors before they turn in papers, however, so that they have a better chance at succeeding.
It is like MB&B301 but less stressful, focuses more on the concepts and how the literature discovered/supports a given model, and there are discussion papers.
This class dives deep into experimental design for MBB experiments. Only take it if you actually want to do graduate work in biochemistry/biophysics.
